file: crates/ctx-cage/src/lifecycle/teardown.rs
behavior: Best-effort deletion of a cage run's per-run directory (rules file, proxy socket, synthesized claude config) after the run completes.
edit_notes:
  - Per ADR-027 hygiene, must only ever remove prep.rundir — never widen scope to other paths.
  - Runs after `run` has already determined the cage's exit code; errors here must not affect or override that exit code.
functions:
  - name: teardown_run
    signature: pub fn teardown_run(prep: &Prep)
    purpose: Removes the per-run directory tree, ignoring any error.
    notes: Failures are silently discarded; not observable to caller.
invariants:
  - Never deletes anything outside prep.rundir.
  - Never panics or propagates errors, regardless of filesystem state.
external_deps: